  "texts": [
    "Then,∆r jℓ = -α ([Σβ ℓ] j + [Σβ j] ℓ) + α 2 β ⊤ j Σβ ℓ.3.",
    "Empirical distribution.",
    "For each column j, let ρ j = 1 N N i=1 δ xi,j denote the empirical distribution of the unwatermarked entries, and let ρ wm j = 1 N N i=1 δ x wm i,j denote the corresponding distribution after watermarking.",
    "Let W 2 (•, •) denote the Wasserstein-2 distance.",
    "Then,W 2 (ρ j, ρ wm j) ≤ α β ⊤ j Σβ j.The above theorem characterizes column-wise differences and highlights how the parameters (γ, δ) influence them."
